    "abstract": "<jats:p>A simple two-cohort SIR like model can explain  the qualitative behaviour of the logarithmic derivative estimations of the covid-19 epidemic evolution as observed in several countries.  The model consists of a general population in which the R_0 value is slightly below 1, but in which a super-spreading small subgroup with high R_0, coupled to the general population, is contaminating a significant fraction of the population.  The epidemic starts to slow down when herd immunity is reached in this subgroup.  The dynamics of this system is quite robust against non-pharmaceutical measures.</jats:p>",
